'''Kerim Alajbegović''' ({{IPA|bs|kěrim alajbêːgoʋitɕ|pron}}; born 21 September 2007) is a professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Midfielder#Winger|winger]] for [[Austrian Football Bundesliga|Austrian Bundesliga]] club [[FC Red Bull Salzburg|Red Bull Salzburg]]. He will join [[Bundesliga]] club [[Bayer 04 Leverkusen|Bayer Leverkusen]] on 1 July 2026. Born in Germany, he plays for the [[Bosnia and Herzegovina national football team|Bosnia and Herzegovina national team]].

Alajbegović started his professional career at Red Bull Salzburg.

A former youth international for Bosnia and Herzegovina, Alajbegović made his senior international debut in 2025.

==Club career==

===Bayer Leverkusen===
Alajbegović started playing football at his hometown club [[1. FC Köln]], before joining [[Bayer 04 Leverkusen|Bayer Leverkusen's youth academy]] in 2021. In January 2025, he signed his first professional contract with the team.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://scsport.ba/kerim-alajbegovic-bosanski-dragulj-koji-osvaja-fudbalski-svijet-nova-zvijezda-bayer-leverkusena|title=Kerim Alajbegović, bosanski dragulj koji osvaja fudbalski svijet: Nova zvijezda Bayer Leverkusena|website=scsport.ba|date=11 January 2025|access-date=12 January 2025|language=bs}}</ref>

===Red Bull Salzburg===
In July, Alajbegović was transferred to Austrian side [[FC Red Bull Salzburg|Red Bull Salzburg]] for an undisclosed fee.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://klix.ba/sport/nogomet/kerim-alajbegovic-predstavljen-kao-novi-igrac-rb-salzburga/250703062|title=Kerim Alajbegović predstavljen kao novi igrač RB Salzburga|website=klix.ba|date=3 July 2025|access-date=3 July 2025|language=bs}}</ref> He made his professional debut in a [[2025–26 UEFA Champions League#Second qualifying round|UEFA Champions League qualifier]] against [[SK Brann|Brann]] on 23 July at the age of 17.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://n1info.ba/sport/nogomet/alajbegovic-debitovao-u-kvalifikacijama-za-ligu-prvaka-ubjedljiva-pobjeda-salzburga|title=Alajbegović debitovao u kvalifikacijama za Ligu prvaka, ubjedljiva pobjeda Salzburga|website=n1info.ba|date=23 July 2025|access-date=23 July 2025|language=bs}}</ref> On 26 July, he scored his first professional goal in an [[2025–26 Austrian Cup#First round|Austrian Cup]] game against Union Dietach.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://faktor.ba/sport/fudbal/alajbegovic-postigao-prvi-pogodak-za-salzburg/226070|title=Alajbegović postigao prvi pogodak za Salzburg|website=faktor.ba|date=26 July 2025|access-date=27 July 2025|language=bs}}</ref> He made his league debut [[SV Ried|Ried]] on 2 August.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://reprezentacija.ba/476279-alajbegovic-debitovao-u-bundesligi-austrije-u-tri-situacije-je-pokazao-kakav-potencijal-posjeduje|title=Alajbegović debitovao u Bundesligi Austrije, u tri situacije je pokazao kakav potencijal posjeduje|website=reprezentacija.ba|date=2 August 2025|access-date=3 August 2025|language=bs}}</ref> On 9 August, he scored his first league goal in a triumph over [[Grazer AK]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://radiosarajevo.ba/sport/nogomet/kerim-alajbegovic-postigao-eurogol-za-salzburg-pogledajte-majstoriju-mladog-zmaja/601151|title=Kerim Alajbegović postigao eurogol za Salzburg: Pogledajte majstoriju mladog Zmaja|website=radiosarajevo.ba|date=9 August 2025|access-date=9 August 2025|language=bs}}</ref>

In September, he extended his deal with the squad until June 2029.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://avaz.ba/sport/nogomet/998497/kerim-alajbegovic-potpisao-novi-ugovor-sa-salzburgom|title=Kerim Alajbegović potpisao novi ugovor sa Salzburgom|website=avaz.ba|date=30 September 2025|access-date=1 October 2025|language=bs}}</ref>

===Return to Bayer Leverkusen===
In March 2026, Bayer Leverkusen announced that Alajbegović would return to the club in the following season on a five-year contract.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://fokus.ba/sport/fudbal/kerim-alajbegovic-nakon-carobne-noci-u-cardiffu-potpisao-za-bayer-leverkusen/3537873|title=Kerim Alajbegović nakon čarobne noći u Cardiffu potpisao za Bayer Leverkusen|website=fokus.ba|date=27 March 2026|access-date=27 March 2026|language=bs}}</ref>

==International career==
Alajbegović represented [[Bosnia and Herzegovina national football team|Bosnia and Herzegovina]] at all youth levels. He also served as a [[Captain (association football)|captain]] of the [[Bosnia and Herzegovina national under-17 football team|under-17 team]] under coach [[Nedim Jusufbegović]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://oslobodjenje.ba/sport/fudbal/reprezentacija/alajbegovic-debi-za-reprezentaciju-bi-bio-ispunjenje-sna-kospo-srce-me-je-povuklo-da-igram-za-bih-1072861|title=Alajbegović: Debi za reprezentaciju bi bio ispunjenje sna; Košpo: Srce me je povuklo da igram za BiH|website=oslobodjenje.ba|date=4 September 2025|access-date=6 September 2025|language=bs}}</ref>

In August 2025, he received his first senior call up, for [[2026 FIFA World Cup qualification – UEFA Group H|2026 FIFA World Cup qualifiers]] against [[San Marino national football team|San Marino]] and [[Austria national football team|Austria]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://radiosarajevo.ba/sport/nogomet/barbarez-objavio-spisak-za-san-marino-i-austriju-dva-nova-imena-obradovala-navijace/602165|title=Barbarez objavio spisak za San Marino i Austriju: Dva nova imena obradovala navijače|website=radiosarajevo.ba|date=18 August 2025|access-date=18 August 2025|language=bs}}</ref> He debuted against the former on 6 September and managed to score a goal.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://reprezentacija.ba/481613-zmajevi-razbili-san-marino-u-gostima|title=Zmajevi razbili San Marino u gostima|website=reprezentacija.ba|date=6 September 2025|access-date=9 September 2025|language=bs}}</ref>

In June 2026, Alajbegović was named in Bosnia and Herzegovina's squad for the [[2026 FIFA World Cup]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://sportske.ba/clanak/barbarez-poslao-konacan-spisak-fifa-i-jedno-ime-otputovalo-u-ameriku-ali-nije-na-listi|title=Barbarez poslao konačan spisak FIFA-i: Jedno ime otputovalo u Ameriku, ali nije na listi|website=sportske.ba|date=3 June 2026|access-date=3 June 2026|language=bs}}</ref>

==Personal life==
Alajbegović's parents were born in [[Bugojno]].<ref>{{Cite web |date=2025-06-23 |title=Kerim Alajbegović pravi transfer karijere, poznata i visina obeštećenja |url=https://sop.ba/kerim-alajbegovic-pravi-transfer-karijere-poznata-i-visina-obestecenja/ |access-date=2026-06-06 |website=Sve Osim Politike |language=bs-BA}}</ref> He has a younger brother, Emre.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2026-03-28 |title=Sportske novosti - Neočekivani junak BiH: 'Babo mi je menadžer, majka živi sa mnom, san mi je Real' |url=https://www.jutarnji.hr/sportske/nogomet/sp2026/kerim-alajbegovic-rekordi-bih-povratak-bayer-leverkusen-15693600 |access-date=2026-06-06 |website=www.jutarnji.hr |language=hr-hr}}</ref>

